<subSubSection pageId="105" pageNumber="106" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1436,666,2012]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,433,1026,1052]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Derivatio nominis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Latin)" baseAuthorityName="Latin" box="[442,598,1026,1052]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Spina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,509,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Spina</emphasis>
(Latin)
</taxonomicName>
— thorn, spine; referring to the long, spine-like terminal setae on leg- IV-6.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="105" pageNumber="106" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1436,666,2012]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,1106,1132]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Idiosoma small, rounded-oval; ridge on dorsal shield apically pointed, caudally dissolved; dorsal shield anteriorly truncated; coxal field relatively short, medial margins of Cx-I and Cx-III mid-sized; genital field broad rectangular, caudally surpassing genital bay; acetabula mid-sized, oval; legs moderately compact, claws on leg-I to -III strong, with single dorsal clawlet and comb-like ventral clawlets; leg-IV-6 with two long terminal setae and several strong, long sub-terminal setae; capitulum compact; palp relatively stout, ventral margin of P2 slightly concave, dorsal margin rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="107" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1436,666,2012]" lastBlockId="107.[151,1436,1151,2017]" lastPageId="107" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,446,1346,1372]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Description, female</emphasis>
(n = 2): Idiosoma rounded-oval (
<figureCitation box="[864,970,1346,1372]" captionStart="FIGURES 257–261" captionStartId="106.[151,269,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[203,1374,187,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-55@106.[191,1396,182,1917]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 257–261. Platymamersopsis spinalis sp. nov., female holotype (MD 61): 257, idiosoma, ventral view; 258, idiosoma, dorsal view; 259, leg-II; 260, leg-IV; 261, capitulum with left palp and chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241007" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241007/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 257</figureCitation>
), grey-bluish, secondary sclerotization light brown-greyish; dorsal shield oval to broad drop-shaped (L/W 461 (486)/353 (373)), ridge on dorsal shield apically pointed, caudally dissolved, glandularia far laterally, Dgl-3 to -5 with stronger setae, Dgl-6 and Lgl-4 far peripheral, with smaller setae; soft integument in dorsal furrow lined (
<figureCitation box="[1140,1247,1466,1492]" captionStart="FIGURES 257–261" captionStartId="106.[151,269,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[203,1374,187,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-55@106.[191,1396,182,1917]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 257–261. Platymamersopsis spinalis sp. nov., female holotype (MD 61): 257, idiosoma, ventral view; 258, idiosoma, dorsal view; 259, leg-II; 260, leg-IV; 261, capitulum with left palp and chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241007" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241007/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 258</figureCitation>
); ventral shield rounded-oval (L/W 510 (523)/402 (412)); coxal field relatively short, broad, Cx-I to -III relatively small, anteriorly only slightly surpassing ventral shield; medial margin Cx-I (45 (51)) and Cx-III (32 (27)) mid-sized (
<figureCitation box="[159,263,1586,1612]" captionStart="FIGURES 257–261" captionStartId="106.[151,269,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[203,1374,187,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-55@106.[191,1396,182,1917]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 257–261. Platymamersopsis spinalis sp. nov., female holotype (MD 61): 257, idiosoma, ventral view; 258, idiosoma, dorsal view; 259, leg-II; 260, leg-IV; 261, capitulum with left palp and chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241007" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241007/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 257</figureCitation>
); Cxgl-2 at posterior margin of Cx-II, relatively far laterally, Cxgl-4 close to anterior margin of Cx- III; Cx-IV caudally bluntly pointed, medial margin passing with rectangular corner to straight caudo-lateral margin, laterally rounded, dorso-laterally extended up to dorsal of Cx-III (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1159,1666,1692]" captionStart="FIGURES 257–261" captionStartId="106.[151,269,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[203,1374,187,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-55@106.[191,1396,182,1917]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 257–261. Platymamersopsis spinalis sp. nov., female holotype (MD 61): 257, idiosoma, ventral view; 258, idiosoma, dorsal view; 259, leg-II; 260, leg-IV; 261, capitulum with left palp and chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241007" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241007/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 257</figureCitation>
), lateral ridge approximately straight (
<figureCitation box="[348,453,1706,1732]" captionStart="FIGURES 257–261" captionStartId="106.[151,269,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[203,1374,187,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-55@106.[191,1396,182,1917]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 257–261. Platymamersopsis spinalis sp. nov., female holotype (MD 61): 257, idiosoma, ventral view; 258, idiosoma, dorsal view; 259, leg-II; 260, leg-IV; 261, capitulum with left palp and chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241007" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241007/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 257</figureCitation>
); genital field large, broad-rectangular (L/W 120 (125)/120 (120)), anteriorly and posteriorly rounded, laterally smoothly convex, caudally clearly extended beyond genital bay; acetabula midsized, oval (Ac1 and Ac3 far remote from anterior and posterior end of genital flaps respectively), setae on genital flaps small (
<figureCitation box="[381,484,1826,1852]" captionStart="FIGURES 257–261" captionStartId="106.[151,269,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[203,1374,187,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-55@106.[191,1396,182,1917]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 257–261. Platymamersopsis spinalis sp. nov., female holotype (MD 61): 257, idiosoma, ventral view; 258, idiosoma, dorsal view; 259, leg-II; 260, leg-IV; 261, capitulum with left palp and chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241007" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241007/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 257</figureCitation>
); setae of Vgl-1 posterior to caudal corner of Cx-IV, Vgl-3 closer to caudo-lateral margin of Cx-IV; excretory pore and Vgl-2 relatively close together, glandularia close to caudal margin of ventral shield; legs moderately compact, leg-I to -III with several strong, pointed setae, claws heavy with single, strong dorsal clawlet and comb-like ventral clawlets (
<figureCitation box="[862,970,1946,1972]" captionStart="FIGURES 257–261" captionStartId="106.[151,269,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[203,1374,187,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-55@106.[191,1396,182,1917]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 257–261. Platymamersopsis spinalis sp. nov., female holotype (MD 61): 257, idiosoma, ventral view; 258, idiosoma, dorsal view; 259, leg-II; 260, leg-IV; 261, capitulum with left palp and chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241007" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241007/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 259</figureCitation>
); leg-IV relatively slender, with many heavy setae, terminal segment slender, with two long terminal setae and a row of four stronger sub-terminal setae (
<figureCitation box="[229,336,1151,1177]" captionStart="FIGURES 257–261" captionStartId="106.[151,269,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[203,1374,187,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-55@106.[191,1396,182,1917]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 257–261. Platymamersopsis spinalis sp. nov., female holotype (MD 61): 257, idiosoma, ventral view; 258, idiosoma, dorsal view; 259, leg-II; 260, leg-IV; 261, capitulum with left palp and chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241007" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241007/files/figure.png" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Fig. 260</figureCitation>
); capitulum short, with short rostrum, dorsal apodemes slender, ventral margin proximally inflated, towards rostral concave (
<figureCitation box="[554,658,1191,1217]" captionStart="FIGURES 257–261" captionStartId="106.[151,269,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[203,1374,187,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-55@106.[191,1396,182,1917]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 257–261. Platymamersopsis spinalis sp. nov., female holotype (MD 61): 257, idiosoma, ventral view; 258, idiosoma, dorsal view; 259, leg-II; 260, leg-IV; 261, capitulum with left palp and chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241007" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241007/files/figure.png" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Fig. 261</figureCitation>
); chelicera typical; palp compact, strong; P2 short, compact, with four dorsal and two latero-dorsal setae, dorsal margin curved; ventral margin slightly concave (
