<subSubSection pageId="107" pageNumber="108" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1436,1151,2017]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,321,1471,1497]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Remarks:</emphasis>
The three Malagasy representatives of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[842,971,1472,1497]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mysorensis">
<emphasis box="[842,971,1472,1497]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">mysorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
–like species group (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davecooki">
<emphasis box="[1221,1436,1472,1497]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Platymamersopsis</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[238,357,1512,1537]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">davecooki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" box="[371,503,1512,1537]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis box="[371,503,1512,1537]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">P. palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" box="[559,678,1512,1537]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinalis">
<emphasis box="[559,678,1512,1537]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">P. spinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are distinct from all African, as well as the other Malagasy species, due to their comb-like ventral clawlets on the claws of leg-I to -III. They share this character with the two Indian species 
<taxonomicName authority="Cook, 1967" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[327,583,1591,1617]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adhika">
<emphasis box="[327,437,1592,1617]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">P. adhika</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[445,583,1591,1617]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref55264" refString="Cook D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cook, 1967" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[642,951,1591,1617]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mysorensis">
<emphasis box="[642,801,1592,1617]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">P. mysorensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[810,951,1591,1617]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref55264" refString="Cook D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Within these species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis box="[1221,1436,1592,1617]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Platymamersopsis</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[242,345,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by a relatively large, rounded idiosoma and very short coxal field, not protruding over the ventral shield; furthermore, the ventral margin of P2 is slightly convex, whereas it is straight or concave in the other species and the central ridge on the dorsal shield is only developed as an anterior and lateral arch. The legs-I to -III of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" box="[543,961,1751,1777]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis box="[543,758,1752,1777]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Platymamersopsis</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[859,961,1752,1777]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are slenderer than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" box="[1223,1436,1751,1777]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinalis">
<emphasis box="[1223,1248,1752,1777]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">P.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[1345,1436,1752,1777]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">spinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" box="[200,435,1791,1817]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davecooki">
<emphasis box="[200,225,1792,1817]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">P.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[316,435,1792,1817]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">davecooki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the terminal setae of leg-IV-6 are shorter than in the latter species. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Platymamersopsis</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[342,433,1832,1857]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">spinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the coxal field is shorter than in the two Indian species (especially the medial margin of Cx-I and Cx-III). The species is separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" box="[766,1186,1871,1897]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis box="[766,981,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Platymamersopsis</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[1083,1186,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davecooki">
<emphasis box="[1247,1272,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">P.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">davecooki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the very long terminal and sub-terminal setae on leg-IV-6. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" box="[971,1406,1911,1937]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davecooki">
<emphasis box="[971,1186,1912,1937]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Platymamersopsis</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[1288,1406,1912,1937]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">davecooki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by an anteriorly very broad and rounded dorsal shield, a very small genital field (in both sexes) and straight ventral margin of P2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
